<runspec version="MOVES5.0.1">
	<description><![CDATA[Crankcase Start Exhaust (process 16) at County (SINGLE) scale — vacuous reference (issue #39).

Process 16 crankcase start exhaust is proportional to start exhaust (process 2).
Canonical MOVES 5.0.1 emits no inventory for process 16 in these single-hour county
runs — it is absent from every captured snapshot's MOVESOutput (0 of ~28 non-empty
snapshots emit process 16). See docs/known-divergences.md §4.5.

The scale gate (scale_canonical_snapshot_diff) therefore asserts a VACUOUS match:
canonical 0 rows == port 0 rows. The port correctly emits nothing; a future
over-emission fails the gate.

Provides a scale-input directory with Starts.parquet (county start activity for
Washtenaw County). Snapshot captured with canonical MOVES 5.0.1 against the Washtenaw
County CDB.]]></description>
